diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index ac633ca..980294e 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -255,0 +256,43 @@ bash scripts/run_qasper_multimodel_write8192_train_and_benchmark_suite_smollm3_3
+### RWKV-MS Memory Adapter Comparison
+
+This fork also supports an experimental RWKV multi-state backend inside the same
+δ-mem adapter interface. The public readout contract stays
+`--memory-readout-mode delta`: both backends write online memory and emit q/k/v/o
+deltas into the frozen attention layer. The controlled variable is only the
+online state update.
+
+| Variant | Flag | Online state | Boundary/write routing | Readout |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| Delta-rule Mem | `--memory-backend delta_rule` | One associative delta-rule matrix per state head | Existing token / message / sentence writes | Shared q/k/v/o delta projections |
+| RWKV-MS Mem | `--memory-backend rwkv_ms` | `rwkv_ms_num_states` HRM-Text-derived RWKV-7 matrices per state head | Fixed chunk slots, controlled by `--rwkv-ms-chunk-size` | Same q/k/v/o delta projections |
+
+The RWKV-MS backend vendors the minimal HRM-Text RWKV-7 projection/readout core
+into `deltamem.core.hrm_rwkv7`, then adds delta-Mem-compatible multi-state
+routing, online state save/load, and q/k/v/o delta injection around it.
+
+Train a matched pair:
+
+```bash
+BASE_MODEL_PATH=/path/to/Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507 \
+TRAIN_FILE=/path/to/agent_memory_qasper_ctx8192_episode_safe_seed42.jsonl \
+OUTPUT_ROOT=/path/to/rwkv_ms_delta_rule_comparison \
+NPROC_PER_NODE=8 \
+bash scripts/run_rwkv_ms_delta_rule_comparison.sh
+```
+
+For a fair comparison, keep these fields identical across both runs:
+
+| Controlled field | Recommended value |
+| --- | --- |
+| Base model | Same checkpoint |
+| Train/eval data | Same files and seeds |
+| Adapter budget | Same `rank`, `alpha`, `delta_heads`, target layers |
+| Write policy | Same `memory_write_granularity` and max write length |
+| Training budget | Same steps, batch size, LR, scheduler |
+| Evaluation | Same LoCoMo / HotpotQA / GPQA / IFEval / MemoryAgentBench scripts |
+
+Use the existing benchmark suite on each trained checkpoint. Prefer the backend
+with better task accuracy at comparable generated-token throughput and GPU
+memory. If scores are close, inspect LoCoMo and MemoryAgentBench first because
+they stress online memory more directly than static QA.
+
